<item>
            <title>[LU-4015] Have ldiskfs handle changing device numbers for an external journal</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4015</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For linux the block device name always maps to the UUID but this is not the case for device numbers. Usually this is not a problem but if you use a external journal and after a reboot the device number change will prevent the MDT from mounting. The proper solution is to add a mount option for ldiskfs to locate the journal using the device path instead of the device number.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>MDT server with a installed RHEL6.4 distro. The MDT uses a external journal.</environment>
